Spec: SpecDD Refactor Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in refactoring code, tests, docs, specs, or project structure while preserving specified behavior.

Owns:
  ./specdd-refactor/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-refactor/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Identify public contracts, scenarios, invariants, dependencies, and forbidden boundaries before refactoring.
  Resolve authority for every file that moves or changes.
  Preserve public contracts, scenarios, invariants, and forbidden boundaries.
  Preserve behavior described by active specs.
  Prefer small mechanical steps with verification between risky changes.
  Run baseline checks before refactoring when practical and rerun them after.
  Update specs, docs, and tests only when the refactor changes structure they describe.
  Resolve authority for a behavior change before continuing when the request stops being a pure refactor.

Must not:
  Move responsibility across spec boundaries without explicit scope.
  Widen dependencies or add forbidden imports.
  Rename public symbols, paths, or contracts unless explicitly in scope.
  Treat behavior changes as refactors.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
  ../fragments/spec-chain-resolution.md.ejs
